    • Field Detail

      • ESCAPED_QUOTE_PATTERN

        private final java.util.regex.Pattern ESCAPED_QUOTE_PATTERN
        Escaped quotes in quoted cells are doubled.

      • buf

        private final char[] buf
        Character buffer for cell parsing. The size limits the largest parsable cell. Specifically, if an unquoted cell and its trailing delimiter exceed this limit, the cell will be split at the limit. Moreover, a quoted large cell will cause a syntax error as when we reach end-of-file without reading a closing quote.

      • in

        private final java.io.Reader in

      • pos

        private int pos
        The beginning of the currently parsed cell in buf. Everything before it is discarded during compaction. The beginning includes the quote for a quoted cell.

      • limit

        private int limit
        The end of valid content in buf.

      • opened

        private boolean opened
        Indicates whether more content might be in the reader.

      • cellLength

        private int cellLength
        Length of a successfully parsed cell. For a quoted cell this includes the closing quote. Set whenever parsing of a cell succeeds. The value should be ignored when cell parsing fails, but is set to -1 to help debugging.

      • delimitedCellLength

        private int delimitedCellLength
        Length of a successfully parsed cell including its trailing delimiter. Set whenever parsing of a cell with trailing delimiter succeeds. The value should be ignored when cell parsing fails, but is set to -1 to help debugging.

      • lastException

        private java.lang.Exception lastException
        Last exception encountered. Saved here to properly implement Iterator.

      • previouslyRead

        private long previouslyRead
